org.eodisp.wrapper.hla
Class ProxyCompiler

java.lang.Object
  org.eodisp.wrapper.hla.ProxyCompiler

public class ProxyCompiler
extends java.lang.Object

Generates a set of classes suitable to implement a federate that corresponds to a given HLA SOM document. May be invoked as a command line application or by using the static compileProxies method (from within an Ant task, for instance).

Adapted from the XRTI proxy compiler.

Author:
Andrzej Kapolka, Iwan Birrer

compileProxies

public void compileProxies()
                    throws hla.rti1516.CouldNotOpenFDD,
                           hla.rti1516.ErrorReadingFDD,
                           TypeConflictException
Generates Java source code for a set of proxy classes corresponding to the object and interaction classes described in the federation description document. Any existing files will be overwritten.

Throws:
hla.rti1516.CouldNotOpenFDD - if the federation description document could not be opened
hla.rti1516.ErrorReadingFDD - if the federation description document is invalid
TypeConflictException - if a type conflict is encountered
